Line baking sheet with parchment paper. Combine Shreddies, walnuts, and cranberries in large bowl. Heat condensed milk and salt in small heavy saucepan over medium-high heat, just to boiling point. Reduce heat to medium-low, simmer 3 min. stirring constantly. Pour over dry ingredients, gently mixing until coated. Spread evenly on prepared pan, forming rectangle approx. 10x12-inches. Bake at 350 degrees F for 15 min., or until light golden brown on surface. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and toffee bits. Cool. Chop into small pieces, approx. 1-inch square.